# Layouts Guide

- **Section width**: See [layout-width.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/layout-width.mdc) and [app/Main.tsx](mdc:app/Main.tsx) — `max-w-7xl` + `px-4 sm:px-6` on section wrappers; root locale `main` stays full width.
- Layouts should provide stable structure first, then decorative polish.
- Prefer backgrounds on the layout container itself instead of positioned decorative children.
- Keep page sections in normal document flow to reduce mobile CLS risk.
- When a layout renders images, supply fixed dimensions and `sizes`.
- Blog and list layouts should not mark repeated thumbnails as `priority`.
- Root and segment layouts should follow Next 16 conventions, including async route params where required.
